===Etymology===
From prefix '''[[hyper-]]''', from Greek for ''above'', + '''[[inflation]]''', from Latin noun of process '''[[inflatio]]''', from perfect passive participle '''[[inflatus]]''', ''expanded'' or ''blown up'', from verb ??

===Noun===
'''hyperinflation'''

# execessive or a great amount of [[inflation]] (technically, increase in the money supply, but sometimes misused to mean increase in prices)

